text:
A couple of inconsistencies in this case:
- First, missing pictures in the camera, that are removed on a computer, not on the camera itself.
- Missing EXIF data on some of the pictures
- At least 3 dead key witnesses
- Pieces of evidence that are found in an extremely wide area, that are in perfect condition, which is inconsistent with the official theory, and seem to be planted there to be found.

text: When you're really lost it"s smart to leave a track. Hopefully the people who are looking for you find this. In the jungle you don't need a bra. So, it's not strange to leave it behind as a track. But it would be likely to hang it on a branch of a tree. Not between some bushes. Finding clothing pieces at unlikely places is bizarre. It"s a strange story....But as a parent for sure i would prefer, to believe and accept the explanation of a deadly accident by crossing a dangerous river. But everybody knows that's not the cause of their death unfortunately.....But as a parent, i wouldn't believe and accept otherwise....It"s the less painfull way to lose your child....

text: Still here in 2018......Something happened to Kris & Lisanne. Does one really think they would just call 911 or 112 when they know when they were near death? The September 11 th attacks in America at the World Trade Centre.  The people who knew they were in trouble and near death would call or message their loved ones.  Not Lisanne and Kris.  Something went wrong or they were led to their deaths.  The FBI said they made a connection between the murder of Catherine Johannet just 35 miles North of Lisanne and Kris. The FBI have never publicly revealed what the connection is but this is all adds up to foul play.  It bears similar resemblance to murdered women Marina Menegazzo and Maria Jose Coni in Ecuador.  I hope one day we can mount another expedition to find more of Kris and Lisannes remains.  Im sure now they are at peace and they are in a better place. x
